# =============================================================================
# DEPRECATION NOTICE - This file is NO LONGER USED
# =============================================================================
#
# All Terraform variables have been migrated to environment variables in .env
# using the TF_VAR_* prefix. This approach provides:
#
# - Single source of truth for all secrets (.env file)
# - Consistent pattern with Ansible configuration
# - Easy migration to secrets managers in the future
# - Better integration with deployment scripts
#
# MIGRATION STEPS:
# 1. Copy .env.example to .env in the project root
# 2. Fill in all TF_VAR_* variables with your actual values:
#    - TF_VAR_hcloud_token
#    - TF_VAR_cloudflare_api_token
#    - TF_VAR_cloudflare_zone_id
#    - TF_VAR_domain
#    - TF_VAR_ssh_public_key
# 3. Source the environment: set -a; source .env; set +a
# 4. Run terraform commands as normal (they will auto-read TF_VAR_* variables)
#
# You can also use ./scripts/deploy.sh which automatically sources .env
#
# =============================================================================

